                            <comment id="13406211" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 4 Jul 2012 00:34:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that adds a check if the current thread is the one we&apos;re trying to stop and, if so, don&apos;t wait.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13406539" author="stack" created="Wed, 4 Jul 2012 14:08:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How does &apos;this&apos; get shutdown then?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13407350" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 5 Jul 2012 18:16:27 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;How does &apos;this&apos; get shutdown then?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It can be by the region server when it&apos;s going down or when a user shuts down a replication stream. Both are coming from other threads.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13412409" author="jmhsieh" created="Thu, 12 Jul 2012 00:25:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bumping to 0.90.8 &amp;#8211; I&apos;m personally not concerned about replication in 0.90.7&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
